ific thinkers and contexts to show in detail the unpredictable, complex and sometimes paradoxical impact of European ideas in an array of colonial settings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIdeology. 0aImperialism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Colonialism & Post-Colonialism.2bisacsh  aBritish empires.  aEuropean political ideas.  aFrench Lamarckianism.  aFrench empires.  aFrench revolutionary ideology.  aIndian nationalist movement.  aJohn Stuart Mill.  aJotirao Govindrao Phule.  aPrivy Council.  aRammohun Roy.  aShyamji Krishnavarma.  aSpanish empires.  aSudratisudras.  acolonial practices.  acolonialism.  acolonized intellectuals.  ahybrid theorization.  aliberal universalism.  apolitical thought.1 aBaumgold, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumgold, Deborah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDaifallah, Yasmeen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzalez, Johnhenry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendrix, Burke A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendrix, Burke A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIbhawoh, Bonny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIdris, Murad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlausen, Jimmy Casas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarwah, Inder S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowse, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Megan C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZastoupil, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb0